 Koninkrijk","Bridge Sollers, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bridge Sollers, Herefordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Bridge Sollers, Herefordshire, England":"Bridge Sollers, Herefordshire, England","Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, England"},"en":{"1215–":"1215–Deceased","1215–Male":"1215–Deceased","1217–Male":"1217–Deceased","1214–Female":"1214–Deceased","1234–1269":"1234–1269","1244–1299":"1244–1299","1246–Male":"1246–Deceased","1195–Male":"1195–Deceased","1199–Female":"1199–Deceased","1195":"1195","1290":"1290","1217":"1217","1315":"1315","1215":"1215","1259":"1259","1269":"1269","1214":"1214","1246":"1246","1224":"1224","1234":"1234","1244":"1244","1299":"1299","1199":"1199","about 1234":"about 1234","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Eardisley, Herefordshire, England":"Eardisley, Herefordshire, England","Bridge Sollers, Hereford, England":"Bridge Sollers, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","Bridge Sollers, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bridge Sollers, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","Bridge Sollers, Herefordshire, England":"Bridge Sollers, Herefordshire, England","Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Solers","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Altered form of   Sauers  , a surname of German origin."],"variants":[{"name":"Sauers","meanings":["German: variant of   Sauer   and, in North America, (also) an altered form of this. The surname <i>Sauers</i> is very rare in Germany. Compare   Souers   and   Sowers  ."]}]},{"name":"George","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Via Old French and Latin, from Greek <i>Georgios</i> (a derivative of <i>geōrgos</i> ‘farmer’, from <i>gē</i> ‘earth’ + <i>ergein</i> ‘to work’). This was the name of several early saints, including the shadowy figure who is now the patron of England (as well as of Germany and Portugal). If the saint existed at all, he was perhaps martyred in Palestine in the persecutions of Christians instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  at the beginning of the 4th century. The popular legend in which the hero slays a dragon is a medieval Italian invention. He was for a long time a more important saint in the Orthodox Church than in the West, and the name was not much used in England during the Middle Ages, even after  St George  came to be regarded as the patron of England in the 14th century. Its use increased from the 1400s, and by  1500  it was regularly among the most popular male names. This popularity was reinforced when  George I  came to the throne in  1714 , bringing this name with him from Germany. It has been one of the most popular English boys' names ever since."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":0,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":9,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":44,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705190,"age":75,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":100,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":113,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When George Solers was born in 1215, in Bridge Sollers, Herefordshire, England, his father, William Solers, was 20 and his mother, Mrs. William Solers, was 16. He had at least 1 son and 2 daughters with Mrs. George Solers. He died in Herefordshire, England."},"et":{"1215–":"1215–Surnud","1215–Male":"1215–Surnud","1217–Male":"1217–Surnud","1214–Female":"1214–Surnud","1234–1269":"1234–1269","1244–1299":"1244–1299","1246–Male":"1246–Surnud","1195–Male":"1195–Surnud","1199–Female":"1199–Surnud","1195":"1195","1290":"1290","1217":"1217","1315":"1315","1215":"1215","1259":"1259","1269":"1269","1214":"1214","1246":"1246","1224":"1224","1234":"1234","1244":"1244","1299":"1299","1199":"1199","about 1234":"umbes 1234","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Eardisley, Herefordshire, England":"Eardisley, Herefordshire, England","Bridge Sollers, Hereford, England":"Bridge Sollers, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bridge Sollers, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bridge Sollers, Herefordshire, 